messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Oh, my God.
Hello?
Hello.
Yeah, what's going on, sir?
Oh, my God.
Sorry, what's going on?
I'm sure.
What is the address?
Lee.
Sir, what street are you on?
At a condo.
Do you know the address?
I'll have to ask this guy right here.
Rob, tell me what's going on. I've got it. Where exactly are you at?
Somebody's been shot. I haven't checked the vitals, but he's down.
Okay, bear with me. Where exactly are you at?
Second and Lee.
Okay, talk to me so I can try to help you. Where exactly are you?
I'm walking out to the curb.
Is the person breathing?
Doesn't look like it.
The condos are between Second Avenue and Lee.
Cardwell Place, 105 Lee Avenue.
I have help on the way. Please tell me what's going on.
Do I need to go back inside?
That's up to you, but can you describe what happened?
There are two bullet wounds on the side of the wall.
Do you know who it is or how you found this?
This apartment. I received a phone call about an injured party inside.
Okay, what apartment is it?
Apartment Four.
Alright, is there a name for the apartments?
Not that I know of.
Okay, and you’re not sure what the apartment address is?
No, sir.
Okay, Rob. I have help coming. Tell me what happened.
I have no idea. I received a phone call saying there was an injured party inside.
Are the injured party male or female?
There are two people, both appear to be deceased.
Okay, can you identify their genders?
It’s a male and a female.
Do you see the officer yet?
I hear the sirens.
I got a call from Wayne, the roommate. He checked on them and found them.
Wayne is the roommate of one of the deceased parties?
Yes.
Okay. Who are you?
My name is Robert Gagney. I received the phone call and came down to check it out.
And Wayne is the one who called you?
Yes.
Can I get off the phone now?
Yes, talk to the officer when they arrive.
